  "text": "Prepubertal female hamsters were superovulated by administration of 40 IU of PMSG, followed by 40 IU of hCG (Sigma, MO, USA) 50 -65 h later. Oocytes were collected from the oviduct 15 -17 h post-hCG and were freed of cumulus cells by treatment with 0.1% hyaluronidase for 5 min. Oocytes were then washed by pipetting through five droplets of TALP supplemented with 5 mM HEPES and maintained up to 2 months in 0.5 M (NH 4 ) 2 SO 4 , 0.75 M MgCl 2 , 0.2 mM ZnCl 2 and 0.1 mg/ml of PVA, pH 7.4, at 48C, until use [CITATION_1] .",
